import torch
from diffusers import StableDiffusionPipeline

pipe = StableDiffusionPipeline.from_pretrained("CompVis/stable-diffusion-v1-4", torch_dtype=torch.float16)  
pipe = pipe.to("cuda")

`text_config_dict` is provided which will be used to initialize `CLIPTextConfig`. The value `text_config["id2label"]` will be overriden.
The config attributes {'scaling_factor': 0.18215} were passed to AutoencoderKL, but are not expected and will be ignored. Please verify your config.json configuration file.
In [5]:
from PIL import Image

def image_grid(imgs, rows, cols):
    assert len(imgs) == rows*cols

    w, h = imgs[0].size
    grid = Image.new('RGB', size=(cols*w, rows*h))
    grid_w, grid_h = grid.size
    
    for i, img in enumerate(imgs):
        grid.paste(img, box=(i%cols*w, i//cols*h))
    return grid
In [34]:
n_cols = n_rows = 2
seed = 120
num_inference_steps = 30
generator = torch.Generator("cuda").manual_seed(seed)
prompt = "infinity symbol icon in blue and bold font"
prompts = [prompt] * (n_cols * n_rows)

images = pipe(prompts, num_inference_steps=num_inference_steps, generator=generator).images
grid = image_grid(images, rows=n_rows, cols=n_cols)
